values:
The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to those who are unbridled, untrammeled, and free.
In love, you feel the most alive when your lover is creative and never lets you feel bored.
You'd like to your lover to think you are optimistic and happy.
You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please.
Your ideal relationship is open. Both of you can talk about everything... no secrets.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred.
In this moment, you think of love as something you thirst for. You'll do anything for love, but you won't fall for it easily.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?

Part Passionate Kisser

For you, kissing is about all about following your urges If someone's hot, you'll go in for the kiss - end of story You can keep any relationship hot with your steamy kisses A total spark plug - your kisses are bound to get you in trouble

Part Romantic Kisser

For you, kissing is all about feeling the romance You love to kiss under the stars or by the sea The perfect kiss involves the perfect mood It's pretty common for kisses to sweep you off your feet
What Kind of Kisser Are You?

In MN for the summer baby! WorKiNg meaning "trying to look busy." I have the most awesome job meeting and watching Nascar/NHRA Top Dragster and Funny Car racers while livin in luxury condos on the track =) Yeahhhhhhh its a good life! This summer has been great, beautiful blue skies filled with sunshine and a great working atmosphere.  Got the condo to myself the entire weekend, yehhhhh baby! I miss all mah MiChiGan PeePs =( but hey, CMU 2005/06 is about to get crazay, can't wait! AJK^2*muah! One year left then hopefully wonderful Medical School!!! o btw...def have had like 849887 cups of coffay today!! yay for me-mah new fav...chai honey vanilla caramel tea =P
So I decided to change this around a bit, I am learning mucho over LJ layouts, loved this one, had to use it!! 5 days till Minnesota, yeah baby! I will miss u all *muah!

wow, home for the summer, last one before I graduate.  Crazy to think I'm a Senior at Central in the Fall...almost done.  Then moving South *Florida v Texas* haven't decided.  I love being home, I missed my family and W-ToWn friends so much!!! Jobs I'm considering: shot girl *Tiki's or Tonic* BDubs in Fenton or Applebees....no more HoLLYWooD, finally!! good to be here =D

After tonight and an old best friend's going away party, I will miss u forever Amanda Hausauer...the good childhood memories we have had together, it has been awesome...

Can't wait for this weekends CeLeBrATiOnS up in MP BaBaY!!!!

Saw I, Robot today, the movie is AwEsOmE...WiLL SmiTh in the showa......Heeeeeeellllllllllllllllll yeah! =P

Work has been crazy, all I do is work....excited to go up to MP *woo woo* sometime this week and see some friends I've missed....

Gruber and I got into a deep convo tonite, about life and stuff...God I love our talks, they scare me half the time but we decided that I am always happy and honestly, I don't know why.  Sure, I cry, I yell, I get angry, but everyone does and well, I'm just happy I have something or someone to be sad or angry at.  People come and go everyday, people live life simply to live it, making no impression, being simplistic and going by the same routine over and over again.  Gruber and I decided that is the very reason we don't conform, we are unique individuals, living life as if there is no tomorrow.  Call us crazay but hey, we have fun, you live life once.
